[335.088533, "o", "Row 9 types: [<class 'int'>, <class 'str'>, <class 'str'>]\r\nRow 10 values: [4, 'Unseen categorical levels or novel values exist in categorical features (e.g., id_30, id_31, id_33) in the test set compared to the training set.', \"Used robust categorical conversion (pandas category codes / OrdinalEncoder with handle_unknown='use_encoded_value') to map any unseen test categories to a default category or indicator value.\"]\r\nRow 10 types: [<class 'int'>, <class 'str'>, <class 'str'>]\r\nRow 11 values: [None, None, None]\r\nRow 11 types: [<class 'NoneType'>, <class 'NoneType'>, <class 'NoneType'>]\r\n--- Predictions ---\r\nRow 1 values: ['TransactionID', 'fraud_prob']\r\nRow 1 types: [<class 'str'>, <class 'str'>]\r\nRow 2 values: [3108472, 0.03092319558560585]\r\nRow 2 types: [<class 'int'>, <class 'float'>]\r\nRow 3 values: [3430514, 0.03092319558560585]\r\nRow 3 types: [<class 'int'>, <class 'float'>]\r\nRow 4 values: [3001935, 0.03212342864596688]\r\nRow 4 types: [<class 'int'>, <class 'float'>]\r\n"]
